result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher J. Henke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Christopher J. Henke in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 9:05 a.m. Agreement stated - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, 10 days jail. Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Brief statement by Defendant. Court will approve agreement. Court costs, no DNA surcharge. Sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, 10 days jail, report no later than 6 p.m. 11/27/15. Huber if applicable. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Court appointed atty fees discussed. Atty Laufenberg to submit final bill. Any excess to be returned to Def.

Defendant Christopher J. Henke in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 11:15 a.m. Agreement stated - Def will plead to charge, however, sentencing to be at later date. Atty Laufenberg reviews sentencing agreement. State and Def agreement with Atty Laufenberg's statement. Def admits previous felony conviction. No contest plea. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Atty Laufenberg satisfied/factual basis. Court finds Def understands, accepts plea and finds guilty of felon possess firearm. Bond continues. Def to continue making atty fee pmts.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 28, 2015 at 09:00 am.
